headline: US oil futures rise from settlement lows as API shows fall in crude stocks
summary: Investing.com -- U.S. crude oil futures rose slightly from post-settlement levels Tuesday after the American Petroleum Institute reported a surprise decline in weekly domestic crude inventories, though sentiment remains fragile amid growing fears about an OPEC+ output hike.

headline: Stocks end third quarter on high note as Dow clinches record, Big Tech extends gains as AI trade rolls on
summary: Stocks capped a historic third quarter — and the S&P 500’s best September since 2010 — as investors bet on economic resilience, Big Tech dominance, and AI-driven growth.

headline: OPEC dismisses reports of G8 production increase plans
summary: Investing.com -- OPEC has rejected media reports claiming that G8 countries plan to increase oil production by 500,000 barrels per day (kb/d), calling these reports "wholly inaccurate and misleading."
